Cosatu General Secretary Bheki Ntshalintshali said retrenchments can not be the first way for companies to save costs. JOHANNESBURG - Labour unions have repeatedly warned of massive job losses on the horizon and with not even a month of this year gone, their predictions are coming true. Massmart, Telkom and several mining companies have all started processes to retrench. READ: Retrenchments: What your employer should do Cosatu General Secretary Bheki Ntshalintshali said the woes of Eskom are disrupting the economy, but does not allow that the rising cost of electricity could be a sufficient reason for job losses in the mining industry. Ntshalintshali said retrenchments can not be the first way for companies to save costs. He called for stricter adherence to rules and regulations.